issue.body:
Task Tracking Tool:

Remember Dr. Menzes mentioned Googlers used sticky notes on white boards? We have an equivalence here on GitHub. Please go to Projects > Basic demo prototyping and you will see 3 columns.
You can then create the tasks you are planning to do in the "Todo" column. Please try to be specific and realistic as possible especially when it comes to the time you think you will need to finish a particular task.  When you are working on a certain task, please drag it to the "in-progress" column, and when you're done, drag it to the "finish" column.

This will help everyone in the team keep track of the progress of our project and remind/help each other out if necessary.
